cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB. 

The paper discusses the development of a methodology for linking speech input to knowledge graphs, which involves natural language processing and semantic annotation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and speech recognition. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which makes cs.IR and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The use of knowledge graphs also suggests that the paper may fall under cs.LG (Learning), which deals with machine learning and knowledge representation. Finally, the paper uses DBpedia, a linked open data resource, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DB (Databases).
